title Government Digital Identity (November 2022)
style wardley

// Anchors — multiple user types: the scenario explicitly lists actors.
// Note: "Bad Actors" is an adversarial anchor; they also have a "need" (to exploit).
anchor Government [0.98, 0.55]
anchor Society [0.98, 0.40]
anchor Citizens [0.98, 0.50]
anchor Corporations [0.97, 0.60]
anchor Entities [0.96, 0.45]
anchor Bad Actors [0.95, 0.30]

// ---- Services layer (what the user actually consumes) ----
component Public Service Access [0.88, 0.55]
component Private Sector Service Access [0.86, 0.65]
component Rule Exploitation [0.86, 0.20]

// ---- Power layer — the social/political capabilities identity enables ----
component Power Over [0.80, 0.50]
component Power With [0.80, 0.35]
component Power To [0.80, 0.30]

// ---- Trust layer — the belief surface that identity operates through ----
component Trust: Benevolence [0.74, 0.30]
component Trust: Capability [0.74, 0.45]
component Trust: Integrity [0.74, 0.40]

// ---- Regulation / rules / exception apparatus ----
component Regulation [0.70, 0.55]
component Rules [0.68, 0.60]
component Exception Handling [0.66, 0.35]

// ---- Claims & credentials ----
component Claims [0.62, 0.45]
component Credentials [0.60, 0.55]
component Verifiable Credentials [0.58, 0.25]

// ---- Identity (conceptual) ----
component Identity [0.52, 0.40]
component Self-Sovereign Identity [0.50, 0.15]

// ---- Identification (how identity is asserted / proven) ----
component Physical Identification [0.44, 0.75]
component Digital Identification [0.42, 0.45]

// ---- Identifiers (the handle) ----
component Mutable Identifiers [0.36, 0.60]
component Immutable Identifiers [0.34, 0.50]
component Connectedness of Identifiers [0.32, 0.30]

// ---- Authority (who issues / governs the identity fabric) ----
component Issuing Authority [0.28, 0.65]
component Centralised Authority [0.26, 0.70]
component Decentralised Authority [0.22, 0.20]

// ---- Transport layer (underneath everything) ----
component PKI [0.16, 0.75]
component Cryptographic Primitives [0.12, 0.80]
component The Internet [0.08, 0.95]

// ---- Dependencies ----
// Anchor edges
Government->Public Service Access
Government->Regulation
Government->Power Over
Society->Trust: Benevolence
Society->Trust: Integrity
Society->Rules
Citizens->Public Service Access
Citizens->Private Sector Service Access
Citizens->Power To
Citizens->Power With
Corporations->Private Sector Service Access
Corporations->Trust: Capability
Entities->Digital Identification
Entities->Credentials
Bad Actors->Rule Exploitation

// Service layer
Public Service Access->Credentials
Public Service Access->Regulation
Private Sector Service Access->Credentials
Private Sector Service Access->Regulation
Rule Exploitation->Rules
Rule Exploitation->Exception Handling

// Power layer
Power Over->Centralised Authority
Power With->Decentralised Authority
Power To->Self-Sovereign Identity

// Trust layer
Trust: Benevolence->Identity
Trust: Capability->Credentials
Trust: Integrity->Issuing Authority

// Regulation apparatus
Regulation->Rules
Rules->Exception Handling
Exception Handling->Claims

// Claims -> Credentials -> Identity chain
Claims->Credentials
Credentials->Verifiable Credentials
Credentials->Identity
Verifiable Credentials->Decentralised Authority

// Identity -> Identification
Identity->Physical Identification
Identity->Digital Identification
Self-Sovereign Identity->Digital Identification

// Identification -> Identifiers
Physical Identification->Immutable Identifiers
Digital Identification->Mutable Identifiers
Digital Identification->Immutable Identifiers
Digital Identification->Connectedness of Identifiers

// Identifiers -> Authority
Mutable Identifiers->Issuing Authority
Immutable Identifiers->Issuing Authority
Connectedness of Identifiers->Decentralised Authority
Issuing Authority->Centralised Authority

// Authority & crypto -> Transport
Centralised Authority->PKI
Decentralised Authority->Cryptographic Primitives
Issuing Authority->PKI
PKI->Cryptographic Primitives
PKI->The Internet
Cryptographic Primitives->The Internet
Digital Identification->The Internet

// Inertia: physical ID is not evolving easily — sunk capital + political capital.
component Physical Identification [0.44, 0.75] inertia

// Evolution movements (scenario, not forecast)
evolve Verifiable Credentials 0.55
evolve Self-Sovereign Identity 0.40
evolve Decentralised Authority 0.45
evolve Digital Identification 0.70

// Notes — strategic tensions the scenario asks for
note Novel — SSI / VC / decentralised auth [0.35, 0.15]
note Standardised — PKI / Internet / PhysID [0.15, 0.85]
note Tension: centralised vs SSI [0.30, 0.50]
note Bad-actor rule-exploitation zone [0.80, 0.22]
